Paul Oniya and his musical group have released a sensational album entitled ‘Yoruba is my heritage.’ The music, which Samuel Gbenga Oniyide produced, is coming two years after the COVID-19 breakout.   Edochie’s first wife shrugs off marriage drama     Faze, Konga, others thrill at Ruggedman’s Foundation night     Adaorah shines at BET awards   “It is a wonderful time again meeting these amazing group band name: Paul and Ceecee Oniya Gospel Music group with the dynamics of cultural African tones. It was an exciting moment for the album launching of this music CD despite the COVID-19 outbreak, the brand name OLD4C Multi-Links reached out to the world with their message of hope to encourage as many people, especially during this trying time,” Oniya said. On the album title, Oniya said, ” The reason the album entitled ‘Yoruba is my Heritage’ is because it reaches out to people of different cultures and at this point, I have to give kudos to Ceecee Ibukunoluwa Oniya aka Oyinbo Yoruba, a British woman who thrilled everyone singing in pure Yoruba language to encourage many people across the globe that, there is hope after the pandemic, despite the observation of social distancing during the COVID -19 outbreak, Music knows no boundaries.”